msgid: In order to catch extremely high speed particles that would otherwise overshoot the kill radius on a single frame, we expand the radius by the speed of the particle and take whichever is higher. This catches even very high velocity particles, but if overshoot is seen, this value can be increased until it disappears.
en: In order to catch extremely high speed particles that would otherwise overshoot the kill radius on a single frame, we expand the radius by the speed of the particle and take whichever is higher. This catches even very high velocity particles, but if overshoot is seen, this value can be increased until it disappears.

Tips:
1.If your spline is not completely in the widget covered region, it maybe culled in some special cases.
2. To avoid the spline been culled, you should keep part of widget's region (location + size) is always in screen.
3. Make "Details->Debug->SplineDebugInfo->DrawWidgetBoarder" checked, It will help debug whether the widget region is in screen.
en:
Tips:
1.If your spline is not completely in the widget covered region, it maybe culled in some special cases.
2. To avoid the spline been culled, you should keep part of widget's region (location + size) is always in screen.
3. Make "Details->Debug->SplineDebugInfo->DrawWidgetBoarder" checked, It will help debug whether the widget region is in screen.
